President Obama has announced a Presidential Delegation to attend the World War II Battle of the Bulge 70th Anniversary Commemoration in Bastogne, Belgium. The delegation will be led by Thomas Nides, Vice Chairman of Morgan Stanley and former Deputy Secretary of the State Department. Other members of the delegation include Denise Campbell Bauer, U.S. Ambassador to Belgium, Brad R. Carson, Under Secretary of the U.S. Army, General Philip M. Breedlove, Commander of U.S. European Command and NATO Supreme Allied Commander, Europe, General Montgomery Meigs, former Commander of U.S. Army Europe and the International Stabilization Force in Bosnia, and Thomas John Brokaw, Special Correspondent for NBC News.